olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
40 g butter
2.5 tbs milk
¼ tsp salt
1 tin chopped tomatoes
⅓ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bunch chives
2 clove garlic
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet chicken thigh

Bring a medium saucepan of lightly salted water
to the boil. Peel the potato and cut into bite-sized chunks. Finely chop the garlic. Slice the
carrot into sticks. Trim the green beans. Cut the
chicken thigh into 2cm chunks. In a medium bowl,
combine the Louisiana spice blend and a drizzle
of olive oil. Add the chicken and toss to coat.
Set aside.

Cook the potato in the boiling water until easily
pierced with a knife, 10-15 minutes. In the last
5 minutes of cook time, place a steamer basket
or colander on top of the saucepan, then add the
carrot and green beans. Cover with a lid and
steam the veggies until tender. Transfer the carrot
and green beans to a bowl and season with salt
and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

Drain the potato and return to the saucepan. Add
the butter, milk and salt, then mash until smooth.
Cover with a lid to keep warm.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over
a medium-high heat. Cook the chicken, tossing
occasionally, until browned, 3-4 minutes. Add the
garlic and cook until fragrant 1-2 minutes.

Add the chopped tomatoes, water and chicken-style stock powder to the chicken and stir to
combine. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat
to medium-low and cook until slightly thickened,
8-10 minutes. Add the baby spinach leaves, then
season and stir to combine.

Finely chop the chives. Divide the mash between
bowls and top with the chicken chilli. Serve with
the steamed veggies and garnish with the chives.